==English==
===Etymology===
[[establish]]ed 1880-85, [[ampere]]+[[hour]].

===Noun===
'''ampere-hour'''
# {{physics}} a [[unit]] of [[electric]] [[charge]], equal to the charge [[transfer]]red by a [[current]] of one [[ampere]] in one [[hour]] through a specified point in a [[circuit]], equal to 3600 [[coulomb]]s.

===Derived terms ===
* Abbreviations: [[Ah]], [[amp-hr]], [[amp. hr.]]

